(145, 'Anupam Kher\'s favorite actor is Ranbir Kapoor!', 'anupam-kher\'s-favorite-actor-is-ranbir-kapoor!', '1', 'Anupam Kher\'s favorite actor is Ranbir Kapoor!', '<p>Veteran Actor Anupam Kher and Ranbir Kapoor met recently in New York. Ranbir Kapoor went there to meet his father Rishi Kapoor who is under treatment. Anupam Kher took a photo and shared it in Twitter captioning about the meeting they had.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He captioned the photo, &quot;It is always delightful to meet one of India&#39;s finest and my most favorite actor and person Ranbir Kapoor. He is affectionate, loving, respectful, compassionate and hugely talented. It was nice walking with him on the streets of New York City and talking about films, life, and life&#39;s lessons.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ranbir Kapoor and Anupam Kher have shared the screen together in the film Wake Up Sid. Last year, Rishi Kapoor announced on Twitter that he is flying to the US for treatment and he is there since then. He has not been seen in any movies after that.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the work front, Anupam Kher was recently seen in a controversial movie &#39;The Accidental Prime Minister&#39;. Ranbir Kapoor is currently busy with Brahmastra which also features Amitabh Bachchan and Alia Bhatt. Alia Bhatt and Ranbir Kapoor are sharing the screen for the first time after the revelation that they&#39;re in a relationship.</p>\r\n', '2ffab67d8080e96f5f4f72216507cc711822788116.jpeg', '', '', NULL, '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 0, 0, 1, 'News', 'T', '1', '0', '2019-04-08 08:29:08', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, '5', 0, '', 'sanghars giri', '', NULL, 0),
(146, 'John Abraham differentiates between Patriotism and Jingoism!', 'john-abraham-differentiates-between-patriotism-and-jingoism!', '1', 'John Abraham differentiates between Patriotism and Jingoism!', '<p>John Abraham is soon being featured in Romeo Akbar Walter. He is these days seen in many patriotic films and the actor believes that this wave going on in Bollywood is worth it. He said it&#39;s totally worthy to have a stream of movies on what people need to see in the current socio-political environment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He said, &quot;Patriotism is something that you must feel in your heart, and you protect it in a certain sensitive, credible, sensible and responsible way in your storytelling. Jingoism is when you wear that on your sleeve. I think there may be some films that may go over the top in trying to be opportunistic, but if there is a wave of films that do address what the country needs to see at this point of time, I feel it&#39;s absolutely worth it.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Talking about the success of the films which revolves around patriotism, Uri: The Surgical Strike, Raazi, Manikarnika: The Queen of Jhansi and Kesari have done the well job in Box Office. John starred Parmanu: The Story of Pokhran also was a narrative story about how India performed nuclear tests around 1998.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He gave the examples of Hollywood movies like &#39;Lone Survivor&#39; and &#39;13 Hours: The Secret Soldiers of Benghazi&#39;. He further added, &quot;I think we have graduated from the Border and LOC Kargil days to a different style of the screenplay that the audience would perhaps find palatable. The audience is also very smart. They know the difference between jingoism and patriotism. So, the minute they will see something jingoistic, they will say, &#39;Listen, drop this. We don&rsquo;t want this&#39;.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Talking about his own projects, he said: &quot;When I did Madras Caf&eacute;, it was because I was very impacted by Rajiv Gandhi&#39;s death. I did Parmanu because it was a story that stayed with me for the longest period of time and I felt how do the youngsters in India do not know what happened in Pokhran. When I am doing Romeo Akbar Walter, it&#39;s another side of our defense forces that I want to show to everyone out here, and I do a Batla House, it&#39;s a very sensitive space.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After Romeo Akbar Walter, John will be seen in Pagalpanti with Anil Kapoor and others. And after wrapping up of Pagalpanti he will be working in Batla House. He talked about Batla House saying, &quot;Batla House is perhaps the most contentious subject in India after Babri Masjid. So, I am actually attempting something where I know the probability of failure is high, but the probability of success is even higher.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Romeo Akbar Walter is written and directed by Robbie Grewal. It released today. It is about a spy who goes undercover in Pakistan. Jackie Shroff, Mouni Roy, and John Abraham are featured in pivotal roles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>John talked about the movie saying, &quot;I wish this film wasn&rsquo;t topical at this time because it&#39;s at the cost of these 40-plus lives of our soldiers that we lost. So, given an option, I would have rather prayed for the lives of our soldiers that have a film that&rsquo;s opportunistic, simply putting it. But the case is such that we made this film over a year ago and we had no idea things would pan out this way. The mood of the country is such that people want to see something on India but at the same time, it&#39;s very important that we explore different facets of the country, if you choose to do so in a sensible way.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>John is also making a biker movie under his own production. The project is not officially announced but John has already admitted it.</p>\r\n', '7e3b50848e503625c43efcdaaafb6b3d1580041445.jpeg', '', '', NULL, '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 0, 0, 1, 'News', 'T', '1', '0', '2019-04-08 08:55:09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, '5', 0, '', 'sanghars giri', '', NULL, 0),
(147, 'Voice your opinion if you are politically aware: John Abraham', 'voice-your-opinion-if-you-are-politically-aware:-john-abraham', '1', 'Voice your opinion if you are politically aware: John Abraham', '<p>Bollywood is always known for controversies that hit media every time. Recently, Kangana Ranaut spoke against her colleagues in Bollywood saying that they didn&rsquo;t take a stand on issues of national interest. And recently, John Abraham too stated a similar statement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He was seen promoting his upcoming film, Romeo Akbar Walter. He said that people should always voice their opinion, provided they are aware of what they are talking about. He said that if a person is politically aware, they should voice their opinion. Otherwise, they would sound like idiots.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He further added saying that one should be careful about what one says and if you don&rsquo;t know something, there&#39;s no harm in admitting it. He said, &quot;If you are saying something that is sensitive, you rather not say it if you are not backed by the knowledge to comment on the subject. The most dangerous thing in this world is low IQ and high confidence. It can&#39;t get worse than that.&quot; Romeo Akbar Walter released today. It stars John Abraham, Mouni Roy and Jackie Shroff in pivotal roles. It is written and directed by Robbie Grewal.</p>\r\n', 'afa8f3c475976b7f8d109a0c10704cba1449479136.jpeg', '', '', NULL, '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 0, 0, 1, 'News', 'T', '1', '0', '2019-04-08 09:02:15', '2019-04-08 09:35:46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, '5', 0, '', 'sanghars giri', '', NULL, 0),
